<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-03-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-03-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="291" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d291">
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">No. 28.</seg></opener>
                            <head><persName type="from">The Duke of Newcastle</persName> to
                                    <persName type="to">Lieutenant Governor
                                Gordon</persName>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Downing Street</hi>,</placeName>
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-03-12"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 12, 1864.</date></dateline></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that,
                                by papers which have reached me from Major General Doyle, it appears
                                that the judge of the vice-admiralty court at Hal fax has decreed
                                the restoration of the Chesapeake and her cargo to the owners.</p>
                            <p>I am happy to take this opportunity of acquainting you that the whole
                                of the proceedings which you had occasion to adopt in connexion with
                                this difficult case have met with the entire approval of her
                                Majesty’s government. I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                            <p rend="right">NEWCASTLE.</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>